modules.description: Parses SVG files into a structured representation and converts them into raster images. Works with SVG data, image buffers, and rendering contexts. Used to load and display vector graphics in OCaml applications with minimal dependencies.

Renders text onto a raster image using a specified font, scaling, and position. It operates on image data and font objects from the Stb_truetype library, modifying a destination buffer in place. This function is used to overlay dynamic text labels or annotations on pre-rendered SVG scenes.
